Act as the predator and click the moths as quickly as you can.
After you eat half the moths the simulation will show you the distribution of coloration for the surviving moths.
Each surviving moth will reproduce. The child moth will be similar in color but is either a little lighter or darker.
The colors are continuous to emulate a multi-gene trait. The simulation is not trying to follow a rigorous genetic model.
